A Shariâ€™a Court in Magajin Gari, Kaduna State, on Thursday, ordered that two men, Nura Usman and Adamu Dauda, be remanded in a correctional facility for allegedly defecating in a mosque. The News Agency of Nigeria reported that the police charged Usman and Dauda with public nuisance andacinciting violence. The judge, Malam Rilwanu Kyaudai, adjourned the case until April 28 for the police to present witnesses. Earlier, the prosecution counsel, Inspector Ibrahim Shuaibu, said Usman and Dauda were handed over to the Tudun Wada Police Station on April 11 by members of the community. He said Usman was caught defecating in a mosque on Alkalawa Road, Tudun Wada, Kaduna, around 2pm. He said Dauda, the second defendant, promised to give Usman N20,000 to defecate in the mosque. 